str2: A teacher, master. From didasko; an instructor.

parse: Verb - Present Indicative Active - 3rd Person Plural
str2: (a) I say, speak; I mean, mention, tell, (b) I call, name, especially in the pass., (c) I tell, command.

parse: Verb - Perfect Indicative Active - 1st Person Plural
str2: To know, remember, appreciate.
Neuter of hostis as conjunction; demonstrative, that; causative, because.

parse: Verb - Present Indicative Active - 2nd Person Singular
str2: I am, exist. The first person singular present indicative; a prolonged form of a primary and defective verb; I exist.
Unconcealed, true, true in fact, worthy of credit, truthful. TRUE.
And, even, also, namely.

parse: Verb - Present Indicative Active - 3rd Person Singular
str2: It is a care, it is an object of anxiety, it concerns. A primary verb; to be of interest to, i.e. To concern.
No one, none, nothing.
For. A primary particle; properly, assigning a reason.

parse: Verb - Present Indicative Active - 2nd Person Singular
str2: (primarily physical), I look, see, perceive, discern. A primary verb; to look at.
But, except, however. Neuter plural of allos; properly, other things, i.e. contrariwise.

parse: Verb - Present Indicative Active - 2nd Person Singular
str2: To teach, direct, admonish. A prolonged form of a primary verb dao; to teach.
The, the definite article. Including the feminine he, and the neuter to in all their inflections; the definite article; the.
A way, road, journey, path. Apparently a primary word; a road; by implication, a progress; figuratively, a mode or means.
A deity, especially the supreme Divinity; figuratively, a magistrate; by Hebraism, very.
On, to, against, on the basis of, at.
From alethes; truth.

parse: Verb - Present Indicative Active - 3rd Person Singular
str2: It is permitted, lawful, possible.
To offer, give; I put, place. A prolonged form of a primary verb; to give.
A poll-tax. Of Latin origin; properly, an enrollment, i.e. a tax.
Of Latin origin; Caesar, a title of the Roman emperor.
Or, than. A primary particle of distinction between two connected terms; disjunctive, or; comparative, than.
No, not. Also ouk, and ouch a primary word; the absolute negative adverb; no or not.

str2: To offer, give; I put, place. A prolonged form of a primary verb; to give.
Or, than. A primary particle of distinction between two connected terms; disjunctive, or; comparative, than.
Not, lest. A primary particle of qualified negation; not, lest; also (whereas ou expects an affirmative one) whether.
